			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am level 54, dont have this spell yet but i have 201 wis and +mana items and i use SoW's on my tanks and seeings how it is only 6ac better than AoF for double the mana, I put AoF on the rest of the crew. Hero on all. I also use symbols when i feel it might be beneficial to my group. Different situations require different tactics and buffs. I have found a few good buffs and some nice chain stunning and guess what folks! Not too many heals required and you have even contributed to the dmg on the mob. Clerics dont just have to buff and heal. Buff, med a bit and stun stun stun, and have fun. Heal when needed if needed.<BR>
Also you can try buffing in shifts. This buff on all then med a little, then this buff on all or these 3 folks first thats likely to take most dmg then the rest next round. We get awesome buffs and they make a difference. Common sense in your situation would tell you the best route to take when buffing and allow you to not be oom all the time.<BR>
<BR>
Shebia - Luclin<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
