	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Inspiration is right about mana being more important than buffs, but wrong about his conclusion.<BR>
<BR>
A cleric's priorities should be:<BR>
1. Keep the group alive, by healing and possibly stunning.<BR>
2. Keep the cleric's mana at 80+%.<BR>
3. Keep the group very healthy (which may not mean<BR>
     full health, depending on the attacks)<BR>
4. Buff the group, in priority:<BR>
   1. tanks<BR>
   2. enchanter<BR>
   3. semi-tanks<BR>
   4. cleric<BR>
   5. others (in emergencies, EVERYONE needs buffs)<BR>
5. Nuke or (chain)stun, (except on planes)<BR>
6. Keep the group 100% healthy.<BR>
<BR>
The big problem with most clerics, including high-level ones, is that they buff in &quot;rounds&quot;, by casting the same buff on most or all people. This is a mistake; it drains the cleric of mana. Cleric mana is much more important than buffs. A cleric should only buff at nearly full mana, and should record who was buffed with what when, and when the buff will run out. This leaves the cleric with enough mana for those heals when they are needed. These records also help the cleric rebuff without asking, or choose the most effective rebuffs when mana is scarce.<BR>
<BR>
One tactic is different for planes than non-planes. In the planes, it is critically important that the cleric be able to camp if the whole raid is going to get wiped out. So when the group is healthy and buffed and the cleric is full mana, it is generally a bad idea for the cleric to stun or nuke, because if things start to go wrong, you don't want a mob to aggro you while you're camping. In fact, at the first sign of danger, the cleric should start to camp, with the cursor hovering over the STAND button. If the &quot;CLERICS CAMP&quot; call comes out, an extra 10 or 15 seconds head start can make all the difference in the world. (Stand and repeat if the call doesn't come.) And yes, it is good for NPC casters to be stuned the planes, but clerics should let others do it.<BR>
<BR>
When not on the planes, it's often good for clerics to chain-stun casters, or at least time a Stun to interrupt a caster. Another good tactic to stop runners is a quick Stun followed by a longer stun.<BR>
<BR>
In conclusion, buffing is good, if the group's health and the cleric's mana warrants it.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
