				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm glad I don't have to group with most of you clerics.  SoW or Aegis goes on the primary tank.  ONLY.  Because casters sit down, they take full dmg regardless of AC when aggroed.  Only hero and maybe symbol goes on the casters for this reason.  When the caster stands up, the tanks have already taunted the mob off (hopefully), and if they haven't, you have a dead caster in a matter of milliseconds.  (As if you can get a remedy off that quick).  More AC on the tank, means less heals you have to put out in a  grind,  or even that the tank will survive while you cast the &quot;read a book while casting&quot; complete heal on em.  Then you have more mana to heal by the time the train comes, and you can save everyone's arse with your &quot;more mana&quot;.<BR>
