				Bulwark of faith might cost more mana over time, but it gives better ac and that is all that counts. I doubt I would use Aegis if I got it. Only time I might use it would be if I meet a friend when I am traveling somewhere and want to give him a buff that lasts for a while. In a full group with enchanter I always have the mana to recast bulwark of faith every time a tank wants it. It seems like verrant put in a lot of spells at high cleric levels that save mana but are a little worse. I would rather see super spells that cost lots of mana than cheap spells that give less power.<BR>
<BR>
A good group imo is cleric, enchanter, warrior, monk, rogue, druid. I have tried lots of groups and this seems to be the best. You have mana, crowd control, speed, slow, tank, damage output, lock picker, snarer, damage shield, evacer, healer, buffer, damage shield, FD and res.<BR>
One might think a pet class could replace some group member, but that's not as effective and you get problems with the pet hitting wrong target. <BR>
<BR>
I cast group heroism and give monk+warrior bulwark of faith. <BR>
Monk, warrior and enchanter get symbol of Marzin.<BR>
<BR>
Only time I have low mana is when we break down to the room we are going to camp for hours. After that I can use DD without problems. I use heroic bond as a group heal.<BR>
When things get bad I switch to just saving lives instead of keeping everyone healed. The druid can heal for a while too. <BR>
