			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OMG, There are a lot of different ways to do your job. Everyones Character has a personalitly and has a different education. Jut like the Doctors in RL, they dont all agree. some it doesnt matter, Some it does. <BR>
<BR>
I am a 52 DE Cleric, I have been playing Slaven since first week of public release. Yes I take my time, and do a lot besides getting exp and all the cool items. I most always have my whole group in SoW as well as Hero and Symbol. I do rounds of buffs if I have full mana, if not just the tanks. in doing this I very rarely go below 20%. There is no need to chain cast buffs, mainly with SoW. Buff till mana is down to 40% sit for 20-30 sec and buff the last 1 or 2 group members. and in a pinch when group is doing insane pulls, like in Seb, where pulls can be constant, skip doing ac buff on the pure casters and even your self. after all what is the differance between 800&amp;830 ac to a mob that has an attack of 1200 or so. hes gonna kick your ass just as fast. ths only differance it will make is maybe one hit more to kill you. Ok so maybe you will be one step from the porter or zone out when you die, but its not worth 300 mana that could have kept your tank alive long enough to kill the beastie. On a true tank 30 ac is a lot to add to 1Kac when your against that same 1200 attack MoB. It will often mean the differance between life and death of the entire group.<BR>
<BR>
In short its not that big of a deal to cast it on everyone. start with your tanks, then your evac person, it just might save them from an interupt. Then worry about the rest of the casters. If you dont cast it on your tanks, Your not worthy of being a a priest and I wish there was a way of banning people who dont have a clue how to play.<BR>
<BR>
As to the guy that said we should be doing more than healing and buffing, please clarify. It depends on the situation, and in my groups, if I have full mana I will cast a DD or stun, but realize we only have 8 slots. In my game, I have 5 or 6 manditory spells memmed: first 3 slots CH,SH,Remedy, after that 2 divine spells, (these 5 are not negotiable, my having that divine memed has saved the entire groups ass many times, it give tanks the time to get it off me before I am dead, then I can heal everyone up and continue). The last 3 are swappable spells. I offten have gate in my last slot.( mainly when doing fast pulls, and I dont have the time or mana to be waisting on nukes. If everything is going peachy I have no problem nuking and or stunning if Im over 60 mana, I chose 60 because at these lvls it can be only seconds before the well broken camp falls apart and that extra mana is needed. As clerics we are VERY inefficiant at melle as well as casting DD with the exception of vs/undead. If your group is so unbalanced that a cleric has to stand up and fight to keep the battle even, Get the hell out of that camp and go somewhere else to get a few lvls first.<BR>
<BR>
I have no problem with doing a clerics share of the damage. but realize a clerics share of the damage is about 2% if even. WE ARE BALANCED, not equal to everyone else. We can change more HP in heals than the entire rest of the group can do in Damage. THAT is what we are there for. Yes we can through in a helping hand when everything is going well. But mana wise if I cast 3 DD Im down to 75% mana, and only did about 1550-1800dmg, against a MoB that has 15k hp.  After this fight Im gonna med to full again and miss the next one. Thats if no heals are needed.<BR>
<BR>
You know how many times I have heard Help in Frenz, our cleric is OOM. and I come to find out its just because he was asked to do a little damage and then all hell broke loose and he had to cain heal the chanter, and blew 50% mana keeping him/her alive. <BR>
<BR>
yes clerics can do a bit of damage, but in a good group doing a bit of Norath cleansing, staying at full mana and saving it all for heals is NOT to be EVER looked down on. THATS OUR JOB!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
lastly,<BR>
<BR>
If a clerics damage is the deciding factor that alows you to win the battle, 1)you have 2 clerics in your group, 2) your group needs to get new members, 3) your farming greenies.<BR>
<BR>
Slaven Soulkeeper<BR>
<BR>
Vicar of the 52nd circle of Hate
